description: An enthralling romantic thriller in the style of Victor Hugo and Alexandre Dumas, The Revenge of the Count Skarbek is set in the world of the romantic artists of 19th century Paris. Famous erotic painter Louis Paulus, returns from beyond the grave in the guise of Count Skarbek to exact revenge on notorious art dealer Daniel Northbrook.
name: Two Golden Hands

description: The follow up to Rosinski and Sente's homage to The Count Of Monte Christo, reveals more of the story of the painter Louis Paulus and the time leading up to the lawsuit against the art dealer Lord Northbrook. In particular it chronicles his adventures on the high seas in the company of a band of cutthroat pirates.
name: A Heart of Bronze

description: A pin-up on every page.

This special issue was made for the 50th anniversary issue of the Dutch magazine 'Zone 5300'. The story was written by Pieter van Oudheusden and drawn by 50 artists. The artists share the story in 17 pages, each artist drew one or more panels using their own unique style to tell the story.

The background image of the cover holds all the names of the artists that contributed their art.

volume.name: Quaestus Of De Waan Der Wijsheid

description: One-shot issue. Title translation: Without Difference. Size 17 x 24 cm, uncolored line drawings. Mostly two panes per page. Only the last page has lettering. 1st edition print run 500 pieces. Cover color is a dark purple, though it looks blue in the picture due to the scanning.
